data.description:
1. Bybit's total assets exceed $19.5 billion, and it still holds more than 450,000 ETH, worth $1.2 billion;
2. The Wall Street Journal: CertiK confirms that the Bybit incident is the largest theft in the history of cryptocurrencies;
3. ZachXBT was the first to detect that Bybit had more than $1.46 billion in suspicious funds outflow last night;
4. Bybit hackers have become the 14th largest ETH holder in the world;
5. Bybit CEO: All withdrawals have been processed, the withdrawal system has returned to normal, and a full report will be released later;
6. Founder of Ethena Labs: Ethena processed the largest single-day redemption and did not encounter any losses or redemption problems;
7. Zhu Su: Affected by the panic of Bybit theft, ETH ushered in a narrative of a record high;
8. Slow Mist Cosine: The Safe front-end was tampered with and caused problems, and Bybit is not an isolated case;
9. Viewpoint: Bybit hackers may use Kanye's coin issuance to clean up stolen funds, and Solana Ecosystem may be exploited;
10. Security community: The Bybit attack involved social engineering techniques, inducing auditors to mistake contract changes for transfers;
11. After the Bybit attack, the total amount of liquidation on the entire network reached US$325 million, and the amount of ETH liquidation was approximately US$87.9 million;
12. SIREN is the winning project of Day 3 of the BNB Chain Meme liquidity plan;
13. OpenSea CEO: The US SEC is about to end its investigation of OpenSea, and NFTs are classified as securities, which is a distortion of the law;
14. Bloomberg: The US SEC withdrew its lawsuit against Coinbase, and the latter has paid US$50 million in legal fees;
15. Franklin Templeton has submitted the spot Solana ETF S-1 document to the US SEC.
